This represents an increase of 34 from Saturday’s announcement of 240 cases. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Health Dr Zweli Mkhize has announced that South Africa now has 274 confirmed cases of COVID-19, representing an increase of 34 from Saturday’s announcement of 240 cases. The Eastern Cape now has 2 cases, the Free State 9, Gauteng 132, KwaZulu-Natal 36, Limpopo 1, Mpumalanga 6, and the Western    Cape at 88, making for a total of 274.   The majority of cases are men at 170 patients, while female patients account for 104 cases. READ: The Health Ministry statement Corona Cases by Janice Healing on Scribd 